Food and Feeding.
Dietary shifts of Northern Fur Seals occur depending on season and foraging area; diets often includes vertically migrating species. Off California and Washington, Northern Fur Seals eat anchovy (
Engraulidae
), hake, saury (
Scomberesocidae
), squid, rockfish (
Sebastidae
), and salmon (
Salmonidae
). Off Alaska, they eat walleye pollock (Theragra chalcogramma), capelin (Mallotus villosus), sand lance (
Ammodytidae
), herring (
Clupeidae
), Atka mackerel (Pleurogrammus monopterygius), and squid.
